# Time Tram – Future You Mirror
# Environment Configuration Template
# 
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your actual values
# DO NOT commit .env.local to version control - it contains secrets
#
# cp .env.local.example .env.local

# ============================================
# REQUIRED: API Authentication
# ============================================

# OpenRouter API Key (Recommended)
# Get your key at: https://openrouter.ai/keys
# Key format: sk-or-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# This provider gives access to multiple AI models (Gemini, FLUX, etc.)
OPENROUTER_API_KEY="sk-or-your-actual-api-key-here"

# ============================================
# OPTIONAL: Model Configuration
# ============================================

# Comma-separated list of image generation models to try in fallback order
# If a model is unavailable in your region, the system tries the next one
# Default models (if not specified):
#   - google/gemini-2.5-flash-image (fast, good quality)
#   - google/gemini-3.1-flash-image-preview (high quality)
#   - google/gemini-2.5-flash-image-preview (preview variant)
#   - black-forest-labs/flux.2-pro (premium quality)
#   - black-forest-labs/flux.2-flex (balanced speed/quality)
#
# Example configurations:
# OPENROUTER_MODELS="black-forest-labs/flux.2-pro,black-forest-labs/flux.2-flex"
# OPENROUTER_MODELS="google/gemini-2.5-flash-image,black-forest-labs/flux.2-pro"
#
# OPENROUTER_MODELS="black-forest-labs/flux.2-pro,black-forest-labs/flux.2-flex,google/gemini-2.5-flash-image,google/gemini-3.1-flash-image-preview,google/gemini-2.5-flash-image-preview"

# ============================================
# OPTIONAL: Application Settings
# ============================================

# Application URL (used for self-referential links, OAuth callbacks)
# Required for production deployments
# Example: https://time-tram.example.com
# For local development, this is automatically set to http://localhost:5173
# APP_URL="http://localhost:5173"

# ============================================
# Quick Start Guide
# ============================================
# 
# 1. Get an API Key:
#    - Option A (Recommended): OpenRouter
#      Visit https://openrouter.ai/keys and create a free API key
#    - Option B: Google AI Studio
#      Visit https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
#
# 2. Copy this file:
#    cp .env.local.example .env.local
#
# 3. Edit .env.local and add your API key:
#    OPENROUTER_API_KEY="sk-or-your-key-here"
#
# 4. Run the development server:
#    npm run dev
#
# 5. Open http://localhost:5173 and allow camera access
#
# ============================================
# Security Notes
# ============================================
#
# - NEVER commit .env.local to version control
# - .env.local is in .gitignore to prevent accidental leaks
# - API keys are kept server-side only
# - Webcam streams are processed locally, never stored or transmitted
# - Generated images may be temporarily cached during processing
#
# If your API key is exposed:
# 1. Immediately revoke it on your provider dashboard
# 2. Generate a new key
# 3. Update .env.local with the new key
#
# ============================================
